{
  "texts": [
    "In these cases, the implicit knowledge supplies the critical information required to explain why the statement is nonsensical, enabling the model to generate a correct explanation and compensate for the limitations of its smaller parameter size.",
    "The comparative improvements achieved with the TIP method highlight the importance of accurate nonsensical concept identification and implicit knowledge augmentation.",
    "ConclusionIn this paper, we introduced a novel framework, Two-stage Identification and Prompting (TIP), aimed to enhance LLMs' ability to generate accurate and coherent commonsense explanations.",
    "The TIP framework consists of two stages.",
    "The first stage identifies the nonsensical concepts of a nonsensical statement that conflict with commonsense knowledge."
  ]
}